description.p:
Bio-distillates feedstock are classified based on their free fatty acid (FFA) content as follows [J. A. Kinast, “Production of bio-distillates from multiple feedstock and properties of bio-distillates and bio-distillates/-distillates blends”, NREL/SR-510-31460 report (2003)]:



    

Refined oils, such as soybean or refined canola oils (FFA<1.5%);

Low free fatty acid yellow greases and animal fats (FFA<4.0%);

High free fatty acid greases and animal fats (FFA>20.0%).
